profile_positions.description:
* Management Coach & Spirit (energy) Coach at Change To Excellence:
• Develop problem analysis, behaviour analysis and determinant analysis;
• Create and monitor the coaching plan;
• Design and evaluate implementation of interventions;
• Execute, (follow up) coaching by reflecting, investigating, training, stimulating and advising.

• Setup & monitor Global Compliance programme Corporate IT;
• Lead and support SOx units (Identity & Access Management, Datacenters, Global Network) w.r.t. Compliancy frameworks, development, implementation and assessment of processes and procedures;
• Execute independent testing, auditing, reporting, monitoring, compliance review & align with SOx units, Corporate IT, Internal Audit & KPMG;
- Scope: IT, AR, AP, Fixed assets, HR, SoD, Purchasing, Treasury  
• Execute Management reviews SOx (world wide) and report to Corporate IT Management;
• IT e- courses roll out: Security Awarenes, Export Control & Privacy;
• Outsourcing T- Systems:
 Contract mapping & screening (with Corporate Legal and internal Philips IT & SOx demands) & contract alignment with Director Compliancy & T-Systems;
 Monitoring follow up on contract issues, operational issues, process improvements & reporting to stakeholders; 
 Monitor execution of vision together with the Director Risk Management about the partnership between Philips and T-systems and execute on this vision 
 Build & maintain a strong network within Philips and T-systems, ensuring a smooth communication flow and identification of issues at an early stage; 
 Lead all monthly and quarterly Management SOx reviews with T-Systems, resolve and escalate issues; 
 Ensure that the service from T-Systems meets the agreed quality levels: KPI’s (incl. review); 
• Setup & implement IT control framework to support central assurance for central IT services world wide (One Assurance Report), including outsource developments;
- Scope: SOx units, Change Management, End User Care, Collaboration & Productivity;
• Brazil IT: setup remediation plan, monitoring & reporting;
• Revision of SOx methodology: advising role w.r.t. updating of IT controls to a.o CobiT;
• Privacy & IT processes: privacy law & regulations (world wide) screening, set up plan (how to incorporate Privacy IT processes- best practice case), monitoring & reporting.

• 	Create, execute and monitor the project plan;
• 	Execute the Risk analysis on Leadmanagement processes ING and within the value chains Mortgages, Private Banking, Personal Banking, MKB, Pensions. Furthermore validate and report;
• 	Create awareness with regards to compliancy: internal (ARIS, process modelling) and external (Law and regulations) by giving workshops;
• 	Create and present proposals to Marketing to solve the critical and high risks on short term.

• Create, execute and monitor the project plan;
•  Update ERM, SOx, IFW awareness bij preparing and giving workshops;
• Mapping of ERM risks and controls to existing ARIS processes for value chains Consumer loans, mortgages, Savings, Customer Information Management, Debit cards, Accounts;
• Handover of project to operation: advise on ERM operational activities;
• Advise on change management process of ERM risk and control changes and adequate registration in ARIS;
• Fine tune ARIS process modelling instructions with regards to risk and control framework.

• Develop Corporate Risk management framework, guidelines, Control Self Assessment, In Control Statement, dashboard, reporting; 
• Report to Director Risk Management, Audit Committee & Board of Directors;
• Audits Holding: plan, prepare (e.g. work program), execute and report;
• Business unit activities: advise, support, coach and monitor;
• Bussiness Social Compliance Initiative (BSCI)-  project: fine tuning process;
• Monitor compliance Corporate Governance; 
• Developer B-WISE tool (issue tracking);
• Member BURM (Business Units & Risk Management) meeting.
